               <p>I am a constable. I saw the three prisoners together in Dartmouth-street, Westminster; 
               <persName id="t17790707-30-person331">
                  Mary
                   Andrews
               <interp inst="t17790707-30-person331" type="surname" value="Andrews"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17790707-30-person331" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17790707-30-person331" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             had the linen in her apron; I stopped her, took her into an alehouse, and took it from her; I sent another constable after the other two. She said she bought it of a Jew, and gave two guineas for it. It was wet when I found it upon her.</p>
               <p>(It was produced in court and deposed to by the prosecutor and Reynholds.)</p>
               <p>To the Prosecutor. Are you sure you never sold that? - This is unkalendered; we never sold a piece to any body unkalendered.</p>
